        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-403",
        "content": "Charles Evremonde, called Darnay, was accused by the public prosecutor as an emigrant, whose life was forfeit to the Republic, under the decree which banished all emigrants on pain of Death.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-low_s-normal_e-low",
